definition.value: Thiazolines (or dihydrothiazoles) are a group of isomeric 5-membered heterocyclic compounds containing both sulfur and nitrogen in the ring.
Thiazolines containing a C=N double bond between the carbon atom 2 and the nitrogen atom.

A branched amino heptasaccharide derivative that is beta-D-Man-(1->4)-beta-D-GlcNAc-(1->4)-beta-D-GlcNAc in which the mannosyl group is substituted at position 3 by a beta-D-GlcNAc-(1->2)-[beta-D-GlcNAc-(1->6)]-alpha-D-Man group and the GlcNAc residue at the reducing end is substituted at position 6 by an alpha-L-Fuc residue.

A macrolide that is 10-deoxymethymycin with the ethyl group at position 12 replaced with an acetonyl group. It is a natural product synthesized by Streptomyces sp. AM4900 with weak cytotoxicity against SKOV-3 and Jurkat cells.
A macrolide that is the N-oxide of 12-ketomethymycin. It is a natural product synthesized by Streptomyces sp. AM4900 without biological activity.
This compound is a tropane ring-containing molecule related to cocaine.  It is a photoaffinity ligand used to label for the dopamine transporter.
An organophosphate oxoanion obtained by deprotonation of the phosphate OH group of 2-aminobenzoyl-AMP; major microspecies at pH 7.3.

A branched amino nonasaccharide compound consisting of a beta-D-GlcNAc residue at the reducing end with an alpha-D-Man-(1->3)-{alpha-D-Man-(1->3)-[{alpha-D-Man-(1->6)]-alpha-D-Man-(1->6)}-beta-D-Man-(1->4)-beta-D-GlcNAc moiety attached via a (1->4)-linkage and two alpha-L-Fuc residues attached via (1->3)- and (1->6)-linkages.

A branched amino decasaccharide derivative that is beta-D-Man-(1->4)-beta-D-GlcNAc-(1->4)-beta-D-GlcNAc in which the mannosyl group is substituted at position 3 by a beta-D-GlcNAc-(1->2)-alpha-D-Man group and at position 6 by an alpha-D-Man-(1->3)-[alpha-D-Man-(1->6)]-alpha-D-Man group, while the GlcNAc residue at the reducing end is substituted at positions 3 and 6 by alpha-L-Fuc residues.
